let you out of our sight.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.551
Like, you'll be back
to your human self in a...

15:22.222 --> 15:25.725
'Wait. Wait! I didn't mean
I don't like your bat self.'

15:25.792 --> 15:27.527
'You're fine as a bat.'

15:28.261 --> 15:29.562
Hmm.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.398
'It says here
that it's legendary'

15:31.464 --> 15:33.833
'for a vampire to come out
of his coffin once a year'

15:33.900 --> 15:36.469
in search of his
long-lost bride.

15:36.536 --> 15:37.971
How romantic..

15:38.038 --> 15:40.107
In a sick, vampiry kind of way.

15:40.173 --> 15:41.374
Look at this.

15:41.441 --> 15:42.875
'An old photo of Steve standing'

15:42.942 --> 15:44.677
in front of a mirror?

15:44.744 --> 15:46.646
Oh... I get it.

15:46.713 --> 15:48.148
Steve can't be the vampire

15:48.215 --> 15:50.217
because he's casting
a reflection.

15:50.283 --> 15:52.819
I may not know everything
about vampires

15:52.885 --> 15:54.887
but I know a lot about mirrors.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.256
It explains more than that.

15:56.323 --> 15:59.126
In fact, I think
I've got this mystery

15:59.192 --> 16:01.028
just about wrapped up.

16:01.094 --> 16:03.796
Now, all we need to do
is catch that vampire.

16:03.863 --> 16:05.698
I sure wish Fred were here.

16:05.765 --> 16:09.069
You know, I think a woman
is better suited for this job.

16:10.370 --> 16:11.871
'Okay, now'

16:11.938 --> 16:14.141
don't move a wink.

16:16.676 --> 16:20.280
'Oh, no! Fred got mixed up
with a rogue gang of bats!'

16:20.347 --> 16:23.150
Like, we've gotta figure out
which one he is.

16:23.216 --> 16:24.617
'You think this is Fred?'

16:27.320 --> 16:29.689
You're right, this bat
does have muscular wings

16:29.756 --> 16:33.093
but this other one looks like
he's formulating a plan.

16:33.726 --> 16:34.894
Huh?

16:34.961 --> 16:37.164
That friendly guy's
gotta be him.

16:38.098 --> 16:40.600
Like, Fred-bat, wait for us!

16:44.637 --> 16:46.039
Where is he already?

16:46.106 --> 16:48.007
I'm perfect
vampire-bride material.

16:48.075 --> 16:49.609
Yes, you are.

16:49.676 --> 16:53.080
Now, I'm sure the vampire
will show up any minute.

16:53.146 --> 16:56.783
Velma, do you think we're doing
all this to trap a real vampire?

16:56.849 --> 16:58.551
No, of course not.

16:58.618 --> 17:01.288
Then why do you have a whole box
of garlic behind you?

17:01.354 --> 17:03.156
It never hurts
to have a backup plan.

17:04.457 --> 17:05.392
It's him.

17:05.458 --> 17:07.694
Now, get out there
and strut your stuff.

17:10.029 --> 17:11.664
- Aah!
- Unh!

